Last Broadcast Date: Mon 28 Nov 2011
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, Martha Flaherty, a Canadian Inuit still suffering from one of the darkest episodes in her people's history. Also, lyrics by Silvio Berlusconi and music by Mariano Apicella - Mariano tells us about their new album. And Japanese cartoonist Misako Takashima, who turned her disappointment in love into a popular comic book. Show less